OL,3,CLeaders call for calm as violence
OL,4,Cflares following Belfast knife attack
OL,6,FPolice and political leaders in
OL,7,FNorthern Ireland have appealed for
OL,8,Fcalm after disorder erupted in a
OL,9,Fnumber of areas following
OL,10,Fdemonstrations in response to Monday
OL,11,Fnight's stabbing attack in Belfast.
OL,13,FProtesters have set fire to a bus in
OL,14,Fthe city and firefighters had to
OL,15,Fremove residents from their homes in
OL,16,Fanother street after flames spread to
OL,17,Fproperties.
OL,19,FA man arrested on suspicion of
OL,20,FMonday's knife attack has been charged
OL,21,Fwith attempted murder.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G1/22
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,308,300,200,140,000,100
PN,30702
SC,0002
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F307A1781053389
OL,3,CLeaders call for calm as violence
OL,4,Cflares following Belfast knife attack
OL,6,FThe 30-year-old accused, who is
OL,7,FSudanese, is also charged with
OL,8,Fpossession of an article with a blade
OL,9,For point in a public place and making
OL,10,Fthreats to kill.
OL,12,FHe is due to appear at Belfast
OL,13,FMagistrates' Court on Wednesday.
OL,15,FAnti-immigration demonstrations are
OL,16,Ftaking place in areas across Northern
OL,17,FIreland following Monday night's
OL,18,Fincident.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G2/22
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
