OL,3,CLeaders call for calm as violence
OL,4,Cflares following Belfast knife attack
OL,6,FPolice Service of Northern Ireland
OL,7,F(PSNI) Assistant Chief Constable Ryan
OL,8,FHenderson said: "Sporadic pockets of
OL,9,Fdisorder have broken out in a number
OL,10,Fof locations across Northern Ireland
OL,11,Fthis evening, including incidents in
OL,12,Fwhich a number of vehicles have been
OL,13,Fset on fire.
OL,15,F"We are urging everyone to remain
OL,16,Fcalm, act responsibly, and avoid any
OL,17,Factivity that could place themselves
OL,18,For others at risk.
OL,26,@pD@QOUwD@AOU
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G6/22
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,308,300,200,140,000,100
PN,30707
SC,0007
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F307A1781053389
OL,3,CLeaders call for calm as violence
OL,4,Cflares following Belfast knife attack
OL,6,F"Officers are on the ground, working
OL,7,Falongside partner agencies, responding
OL,8,Fto incidents as they arise and helping
OL,9,Fto keep people safe.
OL,11,F"We are again appealing for calm and
OL,12,Fask all voices of influence within
OL,13,Flocal communities to encourage
OL,14,Fpeaceful protest and discourage any
OL,15,Finvolvement in violence or disorder."
OL,17,FNorthern Ireland's Justice Minister
OL,18,FNaomi Long said some people had
OL,19,Fignored calls for calm.
OL,26,@nD@AOUsD@AOUwD@eO]
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G7/22
