OL,3,CLeaders call for calm as violence
OL,4,Cflares following Belfast knife attack
OL,6,FNorthern Ireland Secretary Hilary Benn
OL,7,Fsaid: "The scenes of disorder we have
OL,8,Fwitnessed in some parts of Northern
OL,9,FIreland this evening are only damaging
OL,10,Fcommunities and putting innocent lives
OL,11,Fat risk.
OL,13,F"There is no justification at all for
OL,14,Fthis type of destruction and thuggery."
OL,16,FThe victim of Monday's knife attack, a
OL,17,Fman aged in his 40s, remained in a
OL,18,Fserious condition in hospital on
OL,19,FTuesday receiving treatment for
OL,20,Fserious eye, face and back wounds.
OL,26,@oD@GOUuD@AOUvD@gO]
