OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F307A1781053389
OL,3,CLeaders call for calm as violence
OL,4,Cflares following Belfast knife attack
OL,6,F"I understand that last night's
OL,7,Fattempted murder will leave people
OL,8,Ffeeling enraged with emotions from
OL,9,Ffear to anger, but please, please let
OL,10,Fthe PSNI, let the police do their job
OL,11,Funfettered and undistracted by wider
OL,12,Fconcerns there may be about disorder,"
OL,13,Fhe said.
OL,15,FPrime Minister Sir Keir Starmer
OL,16,Fcondemned the knife attack.
OL,18,F"The horrific attack in Belfast last
OL,19,Fnight is sickening," he said.
OL,26,@nD@AOUtD@fO]zD@AOU{D@TO]
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                   G19/22
